// Signing configuration (committed).
//
// Device builds need a DEVELOPMENT_TEAM, but we don't commit a personal team ID.
// Instead, each developer drops their team into Config/Signing.local.xcconfig
// (gitignored). The optional include below pulls it in when present and is
// silently skipped when absent — so the autonomous harness / CI, which only
// builds for the simulator (no team required), is unaffected.
//
// To sign for a real device, create Config/Signing.local.xcconfig containing:
//
//     DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = XXXXXXXXXX
//
// (Find your Team ID in Xcode → Settings → Accounts, or via:
//   security find-certificate -c "Apple Development" -p | openssl x509 -noout -subject
//  — it's the OU field.)
#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"
